Insert content relative to target

Usage: moss edit insert [OPTIONS] --at <AT> <CONTENT>

Arguments:
  <CONTENT>
          Content to insert

Options:
      --at <AT>
          Where to insert: before, after, prepend, append

          Possible values:
          - before:  Before the destination (sibling)
          - after:   After the destination (sibling)
          - prepend: At start of container
          - append:  At end of container

  -r, --root <ROOT>
          Root directory (defaults to current directory)

      --dry-run
          Dry run - show what would be changed without applying

      --exclude <EXCLUDE>
          Exclude files matching patterns or aliases (e.g., @tests, *.test.js)

      --only <ONLY>
          Only include files matching patterns or aliases

      --multiple
          Allow glob patterns to match multiple symbols

  -m, --message <MESSAGE>
          Message describing the edit (for shadow git history)
          
          [aliases: --reason]

      --json
          Output as JSON

      --jq <EXPR>
          Filter JSON output with jq expression (implies --json)

      --pretty
          Human-friendly output with colors and formatting

      --compact
          Compact output without colors (overrides TTY detection)

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
